The paper discusses a system for simulating how adversarial agents interact with a blockchain protocol, which is relevant to computer security (cs.CR) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The simulation system is influenced by algorithmic trading and reinforcement learning systems, which are related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and neural networks (cs.NE).
